    "diffSummary": "Bridged the zca-rust WebSocket Listener into the core. types/events.rs adds IncomingMessage + ThreadKind DTOs (no zca-rust dep). zalo/ builds the Listener from login_info.zpw_ws, maps ListenerEvent::Message into IncomingMessage (mapping confined to the zalo layer), and forwards over an mpsc channel via start_message_listener; it also adds login_with(self_listen), profile_of, and send_text. command/start_listening logs in, spawns the bridge, emits each message as a zalo://message Tauri event, and retains the Listener in ListenerState managed state. The frontend subscribes to zalo://message and renders incoming messages. Verified live: a real message round-tripped through the websocket and surfaced as IncomingMessage (thread_kind=User, msg_id present, is_self=true); the attested smoke sidecar was scanned and contains no credential values or recipient phone number.",
    "changedFiles": [
        "src-tauri/src/command/mod.rs",
        "src-tauri/src/lib.rs",
        "src-tauri/src/types/mod.rs",
